Friday // Sen. Elizabeth Warren takes the Hall stage with a special introduction by #NewYork Attorney General Eric Schneiderman and audience Q&A moderated by Zephyr Teachout. -
📚Relevant Historical Trivia: The Town Hall was designed to reflect the democratic principles of its founders, The League for Political Education (a suffragist group). No Box seats, no obstructed views, giving birth to the term "not a bad seat in the house". Midway through construction, the 19th Amendment was passed, finally granting women the right to vote. The Town Hall's opening took on a double meaning: as a symbol of the victory sought by its founders, and as a spark for a new, more optimistic climate. 📚
